    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "The Linux tarball install instructions mention:\n\n  `export PATH=\"$PATH:/opt/nvim-linux-x86_64/bin\"`\n\nBut it may not be obvious to newer users that this must be added to a shell config file (e.g. ~/.bashrc) to persist across sessions.\n\nSuggestion: explicitly mention that running this command directly will only affect the current shell session.\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-06T13:46:33Z",
